isDirty

public boolean isDirty()
The dirty state in dependencies panel is computed "manually": every field value is compared with the current field value of the corresponding DTO.
And that's because the Field.isDirty() returns true for some unknown reason when the store contains values that render the same string in the combo. (non-Javadoc)

Specified by:
isDirty in interface IFieldPanel
Returns:
true, if the value of a field representing some property of the bound data has changed;false,otherwise
See Also:
